The paper deals with packet scheduling in the presence of adversarial jamming, which is a problem commonly studied in the information theory (cs.IT) and networking (cs.NI) communities. The paper also proposes a new algorithm for this problem, which involves designing and analyzing data structures and algorithms (cs.DS, cs.AL). Finally, the paper includes a lower bound on the speedup of any 1-competitive deterministic algorithm, which is a result in the area of game theory (cs.GT).
